Manchester City playmaker, Kevin De Bruyne has been named Premier League Player for the 2019/20 campaign. De Bruyne beat three players from Liverpool, Jordan Henderson, Sadio Mane and Trent Alexander-Arnold to win the annual award on Sunday. The Belgian international also beat Southampton striker, Danny Ings, Burnley goalkeeper Nick Pope and Leicesterâ€™s Golden Boot winner Jamie Vardy to the award. He was the only Manchester City player to be nominated for the prize. De Bruyne scored 13 goals and registered 20 assists for Man City this season. Premier League 2019/20 Player of the Season nominees: Kevin De Bruyne Manchester City Jordan Henderson Liverpool Sadio Mane Liverpool Trent Alexander-Arnold Liverpool Danny Ings Southampton Nick Pope Burnley Jamie Vardy Leicester